//
// test/preprocess/p03/fail.test — P3 undefined-macro fail-case per
// the FR-037 locked diagnostic strings in
// `specs/002-m1-lex-preprocess/contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md`
// + the "Mandatory diagnostic-string fixtures" table.
//
// FR-037 P3 lock:  `undefined macro reference: '%<NAME>%'`
//
// Per Constitution Principle VIII the failing fixture asserts the
// EXACT diagnostic string. Renaming or weakening this string later
// requires a contract amendment in
// `contracts/diagnostic-output.contract.md` PLUS this fixture's
// update in the same change.
//
// `not %nslc ...` makes lit expect a non-zero exit code; per the
// `nslc -emit=tokens` contract that's exit 1 with the diagnostic on
// stderr and NO tokens on stdout (no partial output).
//
// **RED state**: against the unchanged Phase-3 tree the lexer
// produces tokens for `%UNDEF%` per §13 (e.g., `tk_percent` +
// `tk_identifier UNDEF` + `tk_percent`) and exits 0 — no
// preprocessor exists to detect the undefined macro. Phase-4's
// `IdentSplicer` raises the FR-037 diagnostic.

// RUN: echo 'reg x = %%UNDEF%%;' > %t.nsl
// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %t.nsl 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// FR-037 LOCKED STRING — exact match:
// CHECK: error: undefined macro reference: '%UNDEF%'
